gomodel:SYNGO_5502  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 9: \"PRAF2 is expressed in post and presynaptic terminals of the VTA.\"\n\"Labeling was also observed in postsynaptic contacts. In postsynaptic dendrites the labeling was found in mitochondria and tubulo-vesicular elements. PRAF2 immunoperoxidase staining is present in axodendritic (F) and axo-somatic (G) contacts at the postsynaptic level.\"\n\"Both asymmetric (Fig. 9A, B, D, F, G) and symmetric (Fig. 9C, E) synapses were stained, suggesting that PRAF2 is expressed in excitatory and inhibitory synapses.\". Experimental description: Anatomical and ultrastructural study of PRAF2 expression in the mouse central nervous system (Title of the paper)\n\nPRAF2 antibody (ARP American Research Products, Massachusetts, USA, JM4/PRAF2, #L166), an affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal antiserum raised against amino acid residues 165-178 of PRAF2 (p.4171)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2023-10-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5502" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
